{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 Calibri;}{\f1 Courier New;}}\paperw11907\paperh16840\margl1440\margr1440\margt1080\margb1080\fs22 Electricity Bill Calculator\line \line Assignment Information\line Dar es Salaam Institute of Technology\line Civil Engineering Department\line Module: Programming Fundamentals for Technicians (GST 05117)\line Class: OD24CE-2 | Assignment Type: Group | Assignment No: 3\line Group Number: 11 | Submission Date: March 1, 2026\line \line Group Members\line 1. ABDULAZIZ MAHYORO (240121429579)\line 2. LAWRENCE MMATAMBWE (220121417491)\line 3. ELIAH HANGO (240121476067)\line 4. HUSSEIN OMARY (240121449049)\line 5. ROBERT JAMES (240121479897)\line 6. GIDEON OLANG'U (240121429421)\line 7. MOSES MFUSE (24012317533)\line 8. GLORIA DAUDI (240121453512)\line \line Brief Explanation (One-Page Summary)\line We developed this project as a simple but useful console program to strengthen our understanding of programming fundamentals. This project is designed to receive user values, process them with conditions and calculations, then display final output.\line In this project (Electricity Bill Calculator), c billing system that applies slab pricing for residential and commercial consumers.\line \line How the Program Works\line 1. It shows a clear prompt/menu to the user.\line 2. It accepts and validates user input to avoid wrong values.\line 3. It processes data using conditions, loops, and calculations.\line 4. It prints final results in a readable format.\line \line Concepts Practiced\line - Conditionals and nested ranges\line - Arithmetic calculations\line - Arrays and structs\line - Functions\line - Menu-driven processing\line \line Sample Output (short example)\line === Electricity Bill Calculator ===\line 1. Generate New Bill\line 2. View Bill Records\line 3. Exit\line Choose an option: 1\line Enter customer name: Acme Corp\line Enter units consumed: 150\line Consumer type (R for Residential, C for Commercial): R\line \line Presentation Note\line This mini project is intentionally simple, focused, and easy to explain during presentation.}